{
  "texts": [
    "Then, we obviously have",
    "The proof mainly divides into the two following lemmas.",
    "The first one states that the boundary edges of any community that does not contain v 1 or v 2 -namely the sets of edges E ↑ cyc,k for k ∈ {1,.",
    ", I} -is of size at least 2γ.",
    "The second lemma lower bounds the sum of twice the number of fasteners V fst,̸ =0 that do not belong to the same community as v 1 or v 2, plus the number of boundary edges for the community of v 1, v 2, namely E ↑ cyc,0."
  ]
}